18/09/2006
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Police announced Sunday (17 September) that they broke up a criminal group that was trafficking drugs to Western Europe, predominantly Italy and the Netherlands.
Police said that cocaine was smuggled in capsules via drug mules.
Four people were detained and almost 1kg of cocaine was seized in a series of raids on homes.
In other news, police in Sofia arrested 72 football fans after violent clashes Sunday between supporters of the local teams Levski and CSKA.
The violence erupted before the match started, injuring several people.
(Standart, Darik, Monitor - 18/09/06;
Darik, bTV - 17/09/06)
